'''Hapoel Hod HaSharon''' ({{lang-he|<U+05D4><U+05E4><U+05D5><U+05E2><U+05DC> <U+05D4><U+05D5><U+05D3> <U+05D4><U+05E9><U+05E8><U+05D5><U+05DF>}}) is an [[Israel]]i football club based in [[Hod HaSharon]]. They are currently in [[Liga Alef]] South division.

==History==
The club was founded in 1965.<ref name="22 New teams">[http://archive.football.org.il/multimedia/PDF/Newspapers/hadashot/1965/09-02-1965.pdf 22 New teams (Page 4)] Hadshot HaSport, 2 September 1965, archive.football.co.il {{he icon}}</ref> A Previous club, Hapoel Hadar Ramatayim, which represented the settlements that merged to create [[Hod HaSharon]] in 1964, was active until the [[1962<U+2013>63 Liga Gimel|1962<U+2013>63 season]]. 

Hapoel Hod HaSharon reached [[Liga Bet]] for the first time in [[1975<U+2013>76 Liga Bet|1975<U+2013>76 season]], where they finished second bottom in Liga Bet South A division, and relegated back to [[Liga Gimel]], where they played, until promoted back to Liga Bet in the 1990s. in the [[2008<U+2013>09 Liga Bet|2008<U+2013>09 season]] the club finished second bottom in Liga Bet South A division, and relegated to Liga Gimel, where they spent two seasons, until they finished runners-up in the [[2010<U+2013>11 Liga Gimel|2010<U+2013>11 season]] in Liga Gimel Sharon division,<ref>[http://football.org.il/Leagues/Pages/LeagueDetails.aspx?SEASON_ID=12&LEAGUE_ID=86 Liga Gimel Sharon 2010/2011] The Israel Football Association {{he icon}}</ref> and promoted back to Liga Bet. In the [[2013<U+2013>14 Liga Bet|2013<U+2013>14 season]], the club finished runners-up in Liga Bet South A division,<ref>[http://football.org.il/Leagues/Pages/LeagueDetails.aspx?SEASON_ID=15&LEAGUE_ID=73 Liga Bet South A 2013/2014] The Israel Football Association {{he icon}}</ref> and qualified to the promotion play-offs, and after beating [[Hapoel Bik'at HaYarden F.C.|Hapoel Bik'at HaYarden]], [[Maccabi Ironi Kfar Yona F.C.|Maccabi Ironi Kfar Yona]], and [[Hapoel Rahat F.C.|Hapoel Rahat]], faced [[Maccabi Be'er Sheva F.C.|Maccabi Be'er Sheva]] in the decisive promotion/relegation play-offs. Hapoel Hod HaSharon won 1-0, with a goal by Itay Menachem in the 89th minute,<ref>[http://football.org.il/Leagues/Pages/LeagueGameDetails.aspx?GAME_ID=383633 Hapoel Hod HaSharon Ironi 1-0 Maccabi Be'er Sheva] The Israel Football Association {{he icon}}</ref> and promoted to [[Liga Alef]].

